name: SSI recipients extra check November
summary: Some Social Security recipients will receive an extra check in November due to a quirk in the calendar. Normally, monthly payments are made on the second, third, or fourth Wednesday of each month. However, in November, there are five Wednesdays, which means some recipients will get two checks in that month. The Social Security Administration (SSA) has confirmed that the extra payment will be sent on Wednesday, November 29th. This adjustment affects both Social Security beneficiaries and Supplemental Security Income (SSI) recipients. It's important to note that no checks will be issued in December as a result of this calendar irregularity.
